<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<!--
  RustyNES.entitlements

  v1.9.5 adds the iCloud key-value-store entitlement so the small app config (the
  global Settings scalars: filter, shader params, palette selection, mute, haptics)
  syncs across a user's devices via NSUbiquitousKeyValueStore.

  v1.9.7 adds the CloudKit service + container entitlement so the per-game `.rns`
  save-state slots sync across devices via the user's PRIVATE CloudKit database (see
  CloudSaveStateSync). This is opt-in (off by default) and never blocks local
  save/load. ROMs still stay local / user-provided.

  MAINTAINER CARRYOVER (cannot be set from Linux / checked-in project alone): in the
  Apple Developer account + the Xcode target's Signing & Capabilities, enable BOTH
  the iCloud key-value store AND CloudKit, and create the CloudKit container
  "iCloud.$(CFBundleIdentifier)". The "SaveState" record type is created on first
  upload in the CloudKit development environment; promote the schema to production
  before release. Until provisioned, CloudConfigSync / CloudSaveStateSync gracefully
  no-op (everything stays local). The ids below follow the default
  $(TeamIdentifierPrefix)$(CFBundleIdentifier) / iCloud.$(CFBundleIdentifier)
  conventions, so CKContainer.default() resolves the same container.

  ROMs remain user-provided through the document picker (no broad file access), and
  the app collects no data and does no networking beyond this iCloud sync + opt-in
  netplay / RetroAchievements.
-->
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.developer.ubiquity-kvstore-identifier</key>
	<string>$(TeamIdentifierPrefix)$(CFBundleIdentifier)</string>
	<key>com.apple.developer.icloud-services</key>
	<array>
		<string>CloudKit</string>
	</array>
	<key>com.apple.developer.icloud-container-identifiers</key>
	<array>
		<string>iCloud.$(CFBundleIdentifier)</string>
	</array>
</dict>
</plist>
